text:
Quite a nice little cafe near tuas checkpoint where Mydin supermarket is located. Can see that the owner's pride n efforts in setting up this eatery. Food n drinks are all ok.  I had beef Mee rebus for Rm18, while my friend had seafood Mee goreng (got cockle)

Price point on the high side... But it's aircon n with deco so price naturally higher.

mushroom soup nice creamy yet xso thick, best serve while stil hot 🔥
fried rice 🥩 - very2 yummy.. its portion is big, the rice 🍚 vr soft, fatty2 taste wt tender 🥩 slices
1st ⌚ hibiscus 🌺 tea - 👍. xso sweet wt tangy taste -  feel fresh when serve hot 🔥
environment - cozy, ambience
surely ll come again

------------- 🍌 goreng 🧀 8.Feb.25 -----------
Bought 🍲 again fr this 🍴 . this ⌚ ordering just by Grab 🍲 food. have ordered Pisang Goreng Cheese. Overall, 🤔 could give rate between 4.5 -5.0 out of 5.0.
The banana itself are not naturally sweet - thts good & suits wt my taste.. ☑️This is bcoz thy add toppings which covered later here

Thy fried 🍌 covered wt their own flour -which xso feel salty o sugary ☑️
- x overcooked yet crunchy stil ☑️

The toppings :
** had put some additional notes for them to ➕ more 🧀 anyway.. & thy did ☑️
- slightly condensed milk as a savoury like others sellers ☑️☑️  - for me it's really gooo..ood  yet, more fatty2 creamy taste - due to xtra 🧀 added
- for those looking for 🍌 🧀 which xso sweet savoury stil, can come this 🍴

Last but least, the packaging is better - quite thin paper box yet safe!
As usual, best serve while stil hot ♨️

For a cafe, this place have a quite wide variety of food, which is good. We ordered 3 dish, and our favorite is Afghani Pulao. Their hot Teh Tarik & iced lemon tea also taste just right.

The ambiance also good, and the staffs are nice. Oh, and if you're a fan of football, you'll love their decoration so much.

This cozy, laid-back café has such a welcoming vibe and serves some truly flavorful dishes. I tried the Nasi Goreng Ayam and Nasi Goreng Daging, both paired with sambal, and they were absolutely spot-on! If you’re in Nusajaya, this place is definitely worth a visit. Highly recommend!
Tried the signature afghani pulao… nice middle east styled rice complete with grilled beef, lamb and chicken… all the meat are tender overall satisfying well executed meal… recommend to try…
